markets.rules:
This market resolves based on the box office champion film (the film with the highest period box office) during the 2026 Chinese Spring Festival period, defined for this market as Feb 15, 2026 00:00:00 to Feb 23, 2026 23:59:59 China Standard Time (UTC+8), inclusive.

The “box office champion” is the film ranked #1 by total box office for the defined period, using the period-total box office figures published by the applicable official source. Only period box office totals for Feb 17–23, 2026 are used; lifetime totals or totals outside the defined period do not apply. The market resolves “Yes” for the champion film and “No” for all other films.

Primary source and discrepancies: If the National Film Bureau (China) publishes an official period box office ranking or period box office totals that explicitly correspond to Feb 17–23, 2026, that publication is the sole basis for resolution and prevails over any platform discrepancies. If the National Film Bureau does not publish a period-specific ranking/totals for the defined period, the market resolves using Maoyan Professional Edition’s published period box office ranking/totals for the same dates; if Maoyan is unavailable, Lighthouse Professional Edition’s published period box office ranking/totals for the same dates will be used.

Ties: If the applicable source used for resolution shows a tie for #1 period box office and does not provide an official tie-break, this market will resolve in favor of the tied film whose Chinese title (as displayed by that source) comes first in alphabetical order by pinyin; all other films resolve to “No.”

Finality and publication delays: Only figures clearly published as the period total for Feb 17–23, 2026 are used (not intraday “as of HH:MM” snapshots) when a full-period total is available. Once this market is resolved based on the first qualifying full-period ranking/totals from the applicable source above, the result will not be changed. If the competent authority officially announces that no period box office data for this period will be released, or if no qualifying period ranking/totals are published by Mar 31, 2026 23:59:59 CST, then all film outcomes resolve to “No.”

Resolution Sources (priority order): National Film Bureau official publications (https://www.chinafilm.gov.cn/
); Maoyan Professional Edition (https://piaofang.maoyan.com/
); Lighthouse Professional Edition (https://piaofang.taopiaopiao.com/
) and/or the Lighthouse Professional Edition app listing (https://apps.microsoft.com/detail/xpfm2d67qt093h?hl=zh-CN&gl=CN
).
